The user wants to optimize the page for mobile. Let me read the full current file to understand what needs to be improved for mobile.

Current mobile CSS:
```css
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    header, .filters, .count-bar, footer { padding-left: 24px; padding-right: 24px; }
    .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
```

And topnav:
```css
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    .topnav { padding-left: 24px; padding-right: 24px; }
  }
```

Now I'm identifying the key mobile issues: the header's 60px top padding needs to shrink, the header layout should stack vertically on small screens, the card padding is oversized for mobile, and I should check if the topnav text wraps awkwardly or if the filter bar needs horizontal scrolling support.

